http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Several-IAS-officers-transferred-in-Karnataka/article13975254.ece

The Karnataka government on Friday transferred and promoted several IAS officers. Services of T.M. Vijay Bhaskar, Chairman, Bengaluru Water Supply and Sewerage Board, have been withdrawn from Urban Development Department with immediate effect and he has been posted, until further orders, as Additional Chief Secretary, Urban Development, in the existing vacancy. However, he will continue as Chairman, BWSSB.The other officials who have been transferred are: Mahendra Jain Additional Chief Secretary, Cooperation, has been posted until further orders, as Additional Chief Secretary, Forest, Ecology and Environment, in the existing vacancy. Amita Prasad, Joint Secretary to Government of India, Ministry of Water Resources, Rural Development and Ganga Rejuvenation, New Delhi, has been promoted.Vandita Sharma, Principal Secretary, Infrastructure Development, has been promoted and posted until further orders as Additional Chief Secretary, Infrastructure Development Department.Sanjiv Kumar, Joint Secretary, Ministry of Environment, Forest and Climate Change, New Delhi, has been accorded promotion. Subhash Chandra, Principal Secretary, Rural Development and Panchayat Raj, has been promoted as Additional Chief Secretary, Rural Development and Panchayat Raj.Rajneesh Goel, Principal Secretary, Women and Child Development and Empowerment of Differently Abled and Senior Citizens, promoted as Additional Chief Secretary to Government, Women and Child Development and Empowerment of Differently Abled and Senior Citizens.B. Ramu, Chief Executive Officer, Shivamogga Zilla Panchayat has been transferred with immediate effect and posted as Chief Executive Officer, Zilla Panchayat, Chamarajanagar vice K.H. Narasimhamurthy, until further orders. K. Rakesh Kumar promoted as Chief Executive Officer of Shivamogga ZP